    "visualization_explanation": "The dataset contains three variables: altitude (quantitative, interval scale), gas type (nominal categorical), and volume fraction (quantitative, ratio scale). Synthetic data follows MSIS-86 model patterns with inverse N\u2082/O\u2082 trends (\u03bc=58.2, \u03c3=32.1 decreasing exponentially) versus rising atomic oxygen (\u03bc=47.3, \u03c3=28.9). Colors use NASA's atmospheric visualization guidelines with blue hues for stable molecules and warm colors for atomic species. The areaspline format maximizes data-ink ratio by using smooth interpolation between atmospheric layers while stacking maintains part-to-whole relationships. Cairo's principles are applied through color luminance gradients matching gas molecular weights (lighter blues for lighter molecules). Altitude intervals follow 50km spacing from 0-500km with thermosphere/pause transitions visible at 100km and 300km data points."
